<p><b>What are the three types of consumer decision-making?</b> The three types are nominal decision making, which requires little to no search for alternatives; limited decision making, which requires some but not much of a search for alternatives; and extended decision making, which requires extensive evaluation of alternatives and post-purchase evaluation.</p>